import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const blogContent = `
<p><em>This post outlines the transition of Perqed from a formal verification wrapper into an autonomous hypothesis engine backed by native empirical validation and Hub-and-Spoke orchestration.</em></p>

<h2>Architectural Evolution: The Hub-and-Spoke Model</h2>
<p>Our previous iteration (v2.0) was focused on confirming established combinatorial bounds via targeted simulated annealing. To enable the generation of novel mathematical conjectures, we have transitioned to a Hub-and-Spoke architecture that facilitates interdisciplinary synthesis and rigorous falsification.</p>

<p>In this model, the <strong>Architect</strong> (the central hub) coordinates specialized spokes to ingest literature, generate hypotheses, and execute empirical tests. The <strong>Librarian Spoke</strong> provides the raw material by retrieving structurally diverse papers from a local LanceDB vector store, enabling the Architect to pair conceptually distant domains for synthesis.</p>

<p>For example, in a recent execution exploring maximal graph clique bounds, the system synthesized techniques from fractional matching literature with algebraic structures derived from Hopf Algebras. This interdisciplinary approach allows the Architect to move beyond standard textbook replication.</p>

<h2>The Falsification Loop: Empirical Rigor</h2>
<p>Ensuring the validity of generated conjectures requires a robust falsification loop. We have implemented a multi-stage execution boundary to enforce this rigor:</p>

<ol>
<li><strong>Sandboxed Empirical Validation</strong>: The <strong>Explorer Spoke</strong> executes probing scripts within an isolated Python environment pre-configured with mathematical libraries such as <code>SymPy</code>, <code>SciPy</code>, <code>NetworkX</code>, and <code>Z3</code>. This allows for rapid empirical testing of hypotheses against finite cases.</li>
<li><strong>Automated Self-Correction</strong>: The Explorer Spoke is equipped with an error-recovery loop. If an empirical test fails due to implementation issues, the spoke analyzes the traceback and refines the test code before re-executing.</li>
<li><strong>Specialized Skill Injection</strong>: We have mapped 38 specialized mathematical techniques to their respective domains. The Architect utilizes a Domain Affinity Mapper to inject only the relevant skills into the context of the active spoke, ensuring efficient context utilization and focused execution.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Falsification as a First-Class Citizen</h2>
<p>The engine is designed to prioritize falsification over verification. If a hypothesis is contradicted by empirical evidence—such as a counter-example identified by a SymPy script—the system discards the conjecture before attempting a costly formal proof.</p>

<p>In a recent run analyzing Quandle colorings in the context of torus knots, the Explorer Spoke identified a combinatorial explosion that rendered the initial hypothesis uncomputable. The Architect subsequently refined the research objective, yielding a more focused integer-partition constraint as a tractable open conjecture.</p>

<p>By failing fast and verifying failures empirically, Perqed narrows its research focus to solvable problems, ensuring that the formal verification spoke is only utilized for high-confidence hypotheses.</p>
`;
